    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >General Command is a Napoleonic era turn-based war game.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Take command of the battle field, and strategically maneuver units based on their strengths and the current battle conditions.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><u><strong>Units:</strong></u></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3173160/extras/f9a25c673f5a77117f792f707a4af707.avif?t=1750430264\" width=180 height=181 /></span> </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Infantry</strong> are the foundation of your army.  Although slow moving, they start with the most health and have a decent attack range.  A few infantry units with concentrated fire will pack quite a punch.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3173160/extras/b61c62f77b9a388b725f46054aab7e2e.avif?t=1750430264\" width=180 height=181 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Cavalry</strong> are the heart of any special maneuvers.  They are only effective at attacking in close range, but their ability to traverse the battlefield quickly, and their ability to attack immediately after moving make them great for flanking or charging the enemy.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3173160/extras/f7c79153764899ec4fca2830c027d5c7.avif?t=1750430264\" width=600 height=250 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Canons</strong> set the tone of the entire battle.  They are stationary, but can fire projectiles at long range and rip through enemy lines.  Beware of friendly fire, as these units will fire  if an enemy is in their line of sight.</p>",
